The course is thematically divided into sub-skills, where students practice different sub-skills about each topic. Practical assignments help students to understand different aspects of audio-visual text. Feedback from the teacher and fellow students help to understand current skill level and possibilities to further development.Objectives/eesmärkid:  This is a sub-skill based audio-visual production course, where students practice all relevant sub-skills in terms of audio-visual production. By the end of the course students are able to combine different sub-skills on the level that allows them to create their own stories.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  As the result of the course, the student:  Knows the workflow of audio-visual production Uses different production related sub-skills for creating the whole story  Analyses his/hers levels of skills and need to develop those skills further  Knows criterias of quality audio-visual text  Evaluates the work of oneself and fellow students
